CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 1, 1958, pg. 1, reads: "No Incident - A group of the 20-member skating party rests along the railing of Lexington Roller Skating Rink as other members 'do their number.' The skating party was staged without incident on Jan. 28, under the new policy which no longer bars Negroes.  It was supervised by Mrs. Marion Jordon, executive secretary, and Edward Shelton, staff assistant of the local branch of the NAACP. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of men, women, and teenagers wearing roller skates and leaning against railing, in Lexington Roller Skating Rink
